<br>
Despite the late start, I think we actually managed to get this event going pretty quickly and actually clear out the IGs in short order.  I quickly put together three IG groups and let them do the work of killing them.  While this was going one, Bamana and I gathered the names of those participating and built groups.  As usual, the buffing took a long time, but we are getting a better feel for how this process works and what is expected from those in the buff line and those getting buffs.<br>
<br>
Now, the post mortum on the Vox part of this.  I'm looking for any and all feedback on where I goofed.  We had the Wizards, Tanks, Healers, Enchanters (only one Bard <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) to take her down.  I do think there are a couple things which affected our success (besides the @Home network taking a hit just after we formed the raid groups).<br>
<br>
1)  A number of people where anxious to get the raid going and over with.  These raids take time.  Period.  If you aren't willing to put in the time, don't come.  It only makes it more difficult for the raid overall.<br>
<br>
2)  Some people still didn't listen.  After I made the call to charge, I still saw several pets wandering in the hall.  I'm trying to come up with some way to improve the communication, but all I had last night was the /shout channel.<br>
<br>
So let me have it.  What would you have done differently? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubalendin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balendin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#8E9173>(10/26/00 11:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fcouncilofguildsfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=21.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/wildelf1/bal2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vox Recap (Oct 25)</span><hr size=1> It was very devastating to see that even if we had the amouunt of people to take down Vox we didn't manage to do so. Many times we had a train of giants cause people do not listen to what the leaders say.<br>
<br>
This was my second Vox raid so I am trying to make the comparison between these two. There are a couple of things that I would like to note,<br>
<br>
Try avoid /ooc and use /shout when is something important to say and use CAPS.<br>
<br>
People that don't listen send them a tell or shout &quot;Balendin move back or you are out of the raid&quot;.<br>
<br>
I wish he had more bards, their sv songs are more than great and maybe +55 people could join ONLY to buff us with higher resistances and buffs and not to fight of course. <br>
<br>
A different way to buff: have groups of five where...paladins and rangers cast junk spells, clerics/shamans join and use pack/group buffs, enchanters/druids join for group saves MR/CR e.t.c. when the buffing is done group1 camp...clarity/canibilize/manastone/rods e.t.c. casters gain their mana, buff the second group, group2 camp e.t.c...<br>
<br>
About the tactic that we used: Get ALL the tanks behind the boulder and I mean ALL. When you make sure that ALL the tanks are gathered together give the call. <br>
We moved in 2 groups with about 8 tanks, when Vox casted Fear instantly the tanks became 4 or 5, it is very difficult to hold a dragon with 4 tanks that are going to get slaughtered in less than 20 sec when the other groups are supposed to come. If you have 20 or more tanks attack at the same time, some of them will be feared but many will stay behind and hold the dragon effectively till fear wear off.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I believe that the most important thing is for ALL the tanks to attack Vox at the same time and not in groups.<br>
<br>
Everyone wants to hear the word Victory so let's work on that.<br>
<br>
p.s. We are going back to Vox one of these days to get 6 corpses that are left behind somewhere in the pits.....<br>
<br>
